024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20Modi's%20Third%20Victory%20Is%20Unique%20Not%20Only%20In%20India%20But%20Also%20Globally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ffr7u1ls8_pm-modi_625x300_04_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Modi%20is%20going%20to%20take%20oath%20as%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%20for%20the%20third%20time%20on%20Sunday.%20This%20is%20an%20extraordinary%20event%20not%20only%20in%20India%20but%20in%20global%20democracy.%20He%20has%20not%20only%20equalled%20the%20record%20of%20the%20first%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Jawahar%20Lal%20Nehru%2C%20but%2C%20as%20per%20a%20study%2C%20PM%20Modi%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3Eis%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3Ethe%20only%20leader%20in%20the%20broader%20democratic%20world%2C%20post-World%20War%20II%2C%C2%A0who%20has%20been%20elected%20for%20a%C2%A0third%20consecutive%20term%C2%A0after%C2%A0completing%20the%20full%20tenure%20of%20each%20previous%20term%C2%A0and%20with%20a%20consistent%20vote%20share%20(this%20can%20be%20considered%20a%20mark%20of%20his%20popularity)%C2%A0in%20each%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let's%20talk%20about%20India.%20Till%20now%2C%20Nehru%20had%20been%20the%20only%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20India%20who%20got%20public%20confidence%20for%20the%20third%20consecutive%20time.%20Now%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20the%20second%20Prime%20Minister%20who%20has%20achieved%20this%20feat.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20big%20difference%20between%20the%20victory%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Modi.%20That%20is%2C%20while%20Nehru's%20vote%20percentage%20decreased%2C%20Modi's%20vote%20percentage%20remained%20almost%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20won%20elections%20three%20times%20in%20a%20row%20in%201952%2C%201957%20and%201962.%20Their%20vote%20percentage%20and%20seats%20increased%20in%201957%20compared%20to%201952.%20In%201952%2C%20Nehru%20got%2045%25%20of%20the%20votes%20and%20364%20seats%20out%20of%20489%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%20In%20the%20next%20elections%20in%201957%2C%20Nehru%20won%2047.8%25%20votes%20and%20371%20seats%20out%20of%20494.%20But%20after%20this%2C%20in%20the%20elections%20held%20in%201962%2C%20he%20won%2044.7%25%20votes%20and%20361%20seats%20out%20of%20520%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%20That%20is%2C%20in%201962%2C%20not%20only%20did%20their%20seats%20decrease%20but%20the%20vote%20percentage%20was%20also%20less%20than%20the%20votes%20received%20in%201952.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20vote%20percentage%20received%20by%20BJP%20and%20NDA%20has%20remained%20intact.%20While%20in%202014%20the%20NDA%20got%2038.5%25%20and%20the%20BJP%2031.3%25%20votes%2C%20in%202019%20it%20increased%20to%2044.9%25%20and%2037.7%25%2C%20respectively.%20In%20this%20year's%20elections%2C%20the%20NDA%20got%2043.82%25%20votes%20and%20the%20BJP%20got%2036.6%25%20votes.%20In%202014%2C%20out%20of%20543%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20the%20NDA%20got%20336%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20got%20282%20seats.%20In%202019%2C%20this%20increased%20to%20353%20for%20the%20NDA%20and%20303%20for%20the%20BJP.%20In%20this%20election%2C%20the%20NDA%20has%20got%20293%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20has%20got%20240.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Modi's%20victory%20is%20also%20the%20biggest%20victory%20of%20any%20Indian%20leader%20since%201962.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%201984%2C%20Congress%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20got%2049.1%25%20votes%20and%20414%20out%20of%20541%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20But%20it%20was%20the%20elections%20held%20immediately%20after%20the%20assassination%20of%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20where%20the%20sympathy%20wave%20benefited%20the%20Congress.%20In%20comparison%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20the%20only%20one%20on%20the%20agenda%20of%20good%20governance%20and%20development%20who%20has%20gained%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20public%20for%20the%20third%20consecutive%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20International%20Record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Modi's%20third%20consecutive%20victory%20is%20also%20an%20extraordinary%20record%20on%20the%20international%20stage.%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20the%20only%20leader%20in%20the%20broader%20democratic%20world%2C%20post%20World%20War%20II%2C%20who%20has%20been%20elected%20for%20a%20third%20consecutive%20term%2C%20after%20completing%20the%20full%20tenure%20of%20each%20previous%20term%20and%20with%20a%20consistent%20vote%20share%20in%20each%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20Iran%2C%20Iraq%20may%20call%20themselves%20democracies%2C%20but%20if%20we%20leave%20them%20aside%20and%20talk%20about%20Western%20Europe%2C%20Japan%2C%20North%20America%20(except%20Cuba)%2C%20South%20America%20(only%20a%20few%20countries)%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Israel%20and%20South%20Korea%2C%20then%20PM%20Modi's%20victory%20has%20a%20different%20place%20among%20global%20leaders%20after%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECountry-Wise%20Analysis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20very%20few%20leaders%20in%20the%20democratic%20world%20who%20have%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20win%20three%20or%20more%20consecutive%20elections%20after%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20US%20President%20Franklin%20D.%20Roosevelt%20won%20four%20consecutive%20elections%20in%201932%2C%201936%2C%201940%20and%201944.%20But%20all%20his%20victories%20were%20before%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Canada%2C%20Pierre%20Trudeau%20won%20three%20consecutive%20elections%20in%201968%2C%201972%20and%201974.%20But%20he%20could%20not%20complete%20his%20second%20term.%20Trudeau%20won%20again%20in%201980.%20His%20son%20Justin%20Trudeau%20has%20also%20won%20the%20elections%20three%20times%20in%20a%20row%20in%202015%2C%202019%20and%202021.%20But%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20his%20government%20could%20not%20complete%20its%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShinzo%20Abe%20won%20three%20consecutive%20elections%20in%20Japan.%20He%20achieved%20success%20in%202012%2C%202014%20and%202017.%20Before%20this%2C%20he%20was%20also%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%202006-07.%20But%20none%20of%20his%20governments%20could%20complete%20their%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFelipe%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%20won%20four%20elections%20in%20Spain%2C%20in%201982%2C%201986%2C%201989%20and%201993.%20But%20his%20vote%20percentage%20kept%20falling%20in%20every%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Britain%2C%20Margaret%20Thatcher%20won%20the%20elections%20three%20times%20in%20a%20row%20in%201979%2C%201983%20and%201987.%20But%20none%20of%20his%20governments%20could%20complete%20their%20tenure%20and%20their%20vote%20percentage%20kept%20falling%20in%20every%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Tony%20Blair%20also%20won%20the%20elections%20in%20Britain%20three%20consecutive%20times%20in%201997%2C%202001%20and%202005.%20But%20like%20Thatcher%2C%20none%20of%20his%20governments%20could%20complete%20their%20tenure%20and%20their%20vote%20percentages%20kept%20decreasing%20in%20every%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETage%20Fritjof%20Erlander%20won%20seven%20elections%20in%20Sweden.%20He%20won%20in%201948%2C%201952%2C%201956%2C%201958%2C%201960%2C%201964%20and%201968.%20In%20the%20third%20one%20in%201956%2C%20his%20vote%20percentage%20dropped%20and%20was%20the%20lowest.%20However%2C%20it%20increased%20in%20subsequent%20elections%20and%20reached%20around%2050%25%20in%201968.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJens%20Stoltenberg%20won%20three%20elections%20in%20Norway%2C%20in%202005%2C%202009%20and%202013.%20But%20in%20the%20third%20election%2C%20his%20vote%20percentage%20dropped%20and%20was%20the%20lowest%20in%20the%20last%20two%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Norway%2C%20Einar%20Gerhardsen%20won%20elections%20in%201945%2C%201949%2C%201957%20and%201961%2C%20although%20there%20were%20breaks%20in%20between.%20In%201953%2C%20he%20did%20not%20lead%20the%20election%20as%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20hence%20he%20could%20not%20make%20the%20record%20of%20winning%20the%20elections%20three%20or%20more%20consecutive%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Australia%2C%20Robert%20Menzies%20won%20seven%20elections%20in%201949%2C%201951%2C%201954%2C%201955%2C%201958%2C%201961%20and%201963.%20In%20between%2C%20he%20was%20also%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%201939-1941.%20But%20his%20first%20government%20could%20not%20complete%20its%20term%20and%20its%20vote%20percentage%20also%20dropped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%20in%20Australia%2C%20John%20Howard%20won%20four%20elections%20in%201996%2C%201998%2C%202001%20and%202004.%20His%20first%20government%20could%20not%20complete%20its%20term%20and%20the%20vote%20percentage%20declined%20in%20the%20second%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Germany%2C%20Helmuth%20Kohl%20won%20four%20elections%20in%201982%2C%201987%2C%201990%20and%201994.%20But%20his%20vote%20percentage%20kept%20falling%20continuously%20in%20every%20election.%20In%20Germany%20itself%2C%20Angela%20Merkel%20won%20four%20elections%20in%202005%2C%202009%2C%202013%2C%202017.%20But%20his%20vote%20percentage%20dropped%20in%20the%20second%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndreas%20Papandreou%20won%20three%20elections%20in%20Greece%2C%20in%201993%2C%201996%20and%202000.%20But%20his%20vote%20percentage%20decreased%20in%20the%20second%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20Zealand%2C%20Sir%20Keith%20Holyoake%20won%20four%20elections%2C%20in%201960%2C%201963%2C%201966%20and%201969.%20But%20his%20vote%20percentage%20dropped%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELee%20Kwan%20Yew%20won%20six%20elections%20in%20Singapore%20in%201968%2C%201972%2C%201976%2C%201980%2C%201984%20and%201988.%20But%20the%20vote%20percentage%20declined%20in%20the%20second%2C%20fourth%20and%20fifth%20terms.%20Goh%20Chok%20Tong%20won%20three%20elections%20in%20Singapore%20in%201991%2C%201997%20and%202001.%20But%20his%20second%20term%20was%20short.%20Lee%20Hsien%20Loong%20won%20four%20elections%20in%20Singapore%20itself.%20He%20won%20in%202006%2C%202011%2C%202015%2C%202020.%20But%20the%20vote%20percentage%20declined%20in%20the%20second%20and%20fourth%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20Narendra%20Modi's%20achievement%20is%20extraordinary.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20shining%20example%20of%20India's%20strong%20democracy%20and%20fair%20and%20transparent%20electoral%20process%20at%20the%20global%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Akhilesh%20Sharma%20is%20Executive%20Editor%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717862700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ffr7u1ls8_pm-modi_625x300_04_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-modis-third-victory-is-unique-not-only-in-india-but-also-globally-5847443%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Narendra%20Modi%20is%20the%20only%20leader%20in%20a%20major%20international%20global%20democracy%20since%20the%20Second%20World%20War%20to%20have%20a%20vote%20percentage%20(this%20can%20be%20considered%20a%20measure%20of%20popularity)%20that's%20more%20or%20less%20intact%20despite%20serving%20two%20terms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-modis-third-victory-is-unique-not-only-in-india-but-also-globally-5847443%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Julia%20Louis-Dreyfus%20on%20Her%20%E2%80%98Cuckoo%20Bananas%E2%80%99%20New%20Film%20%E2%80%98Tuesday%2C%E2%80%99%20Why%20%E2%80%98Seinfeld%E2%80%99%20Finale%20Backlash%20Never%20Bothered%20Her%20and%20Why%20a%