unched%20variants%20of%20the%20J-15%2C%20carrier-based%20early%20warning%20and%20control%20(AEW%26amp%3BC)%20aircraft%20like%20the%20KJ-600%2C%20and%20a%20carrier%20variant%20of%20the%20J-35%20stealth%20fighter%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20which%20is%20still%20experimental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20added%20that%20the%20air%20wing%20on%20the%20Fujian%2C%20believed%20to%20be%20approximately%2060%20aircraft%2C%20will%20also%20be%20a%20jump%20up%20from%20the%20air%20wings%20of%20the%20Liaoning%20and%20Shandong%2C%20which%20carry%2024%20to%2032%20fighter%20jets%20and%2012%20to%2017%20helicopters%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226509%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20J-15%20fighter%20taking%20off%20from%20aircraft%20carrier%20Shandong%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6658e128cc442a2f676c6fa9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20J-15%20fighter%20takes%20off%20from%20aircraft%20carrier%20Shandong%20during%20the%20combat%20readiness%20patrol%20and%20military%20exercises%20around%20Taiwan.%3Cp%3EAn%20Ni%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20China%20moved%20from%20the%20ski-jump%20style%20to%20the%20catapult%20indicates%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20it%20likely%20prioritized%20employing%20proven%20capabilities%20first%20before%20moving%20onto%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-testing-catapults-with-heavy-cars-on-new-navy-supercarrier-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvanced%20Western-style%20ones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20approach%20appears%20to%20have%20accelerated%20China's%20ability%20to%20field%20new%20technologies%20and%20bought%20it%20time%20to%20work%20through%20any%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Fujian%20isn't%20using%20steam-powered%20catapults%2C%26quot%3B%20Snodgrass%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20leaped%20past%20that%20technology%20to%20pursue%20an%20electromagnetic%20launch%20system%26quot%3B%20like%20the%20US%20Navy's%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford.%20The%20Fujian%20hosts%20three%20catapults%20on%20its%20deck%2C%20presumably%20giving%20it%20a%20higher%20sortie%20generation%20rate%20than%20the%20Liaoning%20and%20Shandong%20carriers%2C%20both%20of%20which%20could%20only%20launch%20one%20aircraft%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20%26quot%3Breinforces%20the%20view%20that%20China%20continues%20to%20demonstrate%20an%20ability%20to%20field%2C%20test%2C%20refine%2C%20and%20develop%20capabilities%20faster%20than%20other%20nations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20China%20plans%20to%20build%20six%20carriers%20by%202035%2C%20but%20very%20few%20details%20on%20Fujian's%20successors%20have%20been%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba377ba8-0f4b-4901-abe2-a665deb37287%5C%22%3EPeople%20are%20key%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fe13300d366e60018099843%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESailors%20aboard%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20observe%20flight%20operations%2C%20July%2031%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FMCS1%20Gary%20A%20Prill%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20China%20is%20going%20full%20steam%20ahead%20in%20its%20development%20of%20aircraft%20carriers%20doesn't%20mean%20they're%20catching%20up%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20US%20Navy's%20nuclear-powered%20Nimitz%20and%20Ford-class%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20the%20Fujian%20is%20conventionally%20powered%2C%20meaning%20it%20will%20need%20to%20refuel.%20As%20with%20the%20Liaoning%20and%20Shandong%2C%20this%20can%20affect%20how%20far%20the%20ship%20travels%20from%20port%20and%20make%20logistics%20operations%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20China%20only%20has%20three%20carriers%2C%20the%20latest%20still%20undergoing%20sea%20