%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAt%20one%20time%2C%20Disney%20was%20the%20only%20person%20who%20was%20allowed%20to%20make%20a%20cartoon%20in%20full%20Technicolor.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221158%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mickey%20Mouse%20poster%20circa%201930s.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666083eecc442a2f676e238b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221818%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMickey%20Mouse%20poster%20circa%201930s.%3Cp%3ELMPC%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201932%2C%20Disney%20produced%20the%20first-ever%20full-color%20Technicolor%20cartoon%2C%20%26quot%3BFlowers%20and%20Trees%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20from%20then%20until%20the%20end%20of%201935%20he%20had%20exclusive%20rights%20to%20use%20the%20new%20three-color%20animation%20process%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2014%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Ftechnicolors-major-milestones-after-100-years-of-innovation-1201346644%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVariety%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20other%20color%20cartoons%20had%20to%20be%20made%20the%20old%20way%2C%20using%20the%20out-of-date%20two-color%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDisney%20was%20laughed%20at%20for%20wanting%20to%20create%20a%20feature-length%20animated%20film.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222988%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Snow%20White%20and%20the%20Seven%20Dwarfs%20lobbycard%20from%201937.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6660857ad0b8e1c832cc233b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222241%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESnow%20White%20and%20the%20Seven%20Dwarfs%20lobbycard%20from%201937.%3Cp%3ELMPC%2FContributor%2FLMPC%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20a%20time%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-live-action-remakes-2017-2%5C%22%3Eanimated%20films%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20considered%20a%20ridiculous%20concept%2C%20but%20when%20Walt%20Disney%20set%20out%20to%20create%20the%20first%20feature-length%20cartoon%20in%201937%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-snow-white-2024-cast-release-date-controversy-2023-8%5C%22%3ESnow%20White%20and%20the%20Seven%20Dwarfs%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20laughed%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20became%20known%20in%20the%20industry%20as%20%26quot%3BDisney's%20Folly%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsheboyganmuseum.org%2Fthe-fairest-of-them-all-walt-disneys-snow-white-and-the-seven-dwarfs-1937%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Sheboygan%20County%20Historical%20Society%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20surprised%20everyone%20when%20%26quot%3BSnow%20White%26quot%3B%20premiered%20to%20packed%20houses%2C%20and%20Disney%20won%20an%20honorary%20Academy%20Award%20(and%20eight%20Oscar%20statuettes%3A%20one%20normal-sized%20and%20seven%20dwarf-sized)%20for%20the%20breakthrough%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20tables%20soon%20turned%20%E2%80%94%20Walt%20Disney%20still%20holds%20the%20record%20for%20most%20Academy%20Award%20wins%20ever.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Walt%20Disney's%20eight%20Oscars%20(one%20regular-sized%2C%20and%20seven%20in%20miniature)%20for%20%26quot%3BSnow%20White%20and%20the%20Seven%20Dwarves%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a21cca83339b09f008b4681%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalt%20Disney's%20eight%20Oscar%20statuettes.%3Cp%3EDavid%20McNew%2FGettyImages%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWalt%20Disney%20went%20on%20to%20win%2022%20Academy%20Awards%20throughout%20his%20career%20and%20still%20holds%20the%20record%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-won