ing%20emergency%20response%20options%20in%20the%20event%20of%20future%20Russian%20aggression%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20confirmed%20offer%20that%20will%20come%20at%20this%20year's%20July%20summit%20will%20be%20an%20agreement%20from%20NATO%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20expand%20cooperation%20in%20defence%20technology%20and%20intelligence%20exchange%20regarding%20Russia's%20electronic%20warfare%20capabilities%2C%20NATO%20Assistant%20Secretary%20General%20David%20van%20Weel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-06-06%2Fnato-to-expand-defense-tech-intelligence-sharing-with-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20reporters%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Meister%20said%20that%20the%20lack%20of%20stable%20military%20aid%20commitments%20beyond%202024%20%26quot%3Breflects%20the%20current%20challenges%20faced%20by%20Ukraine%20and%20its%20allies%20and%20divisions%20within%20NATO.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20these%20packages%20are%20a%20reaction%20to%20the%20situation%20that%20there%20is%20no%20agreement%20among%20the%20member%20states%20for%20NATO%20integration.%20Each%20NATO%20member%20state%20has%20to%20do%20%26quot%3Bmore%20planning%20for%20long-term%20support%20for%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20on%20its%20own%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy's%20office%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20servicemen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661a690a3f923f7dab07b941%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20servicemen%20fighting%20off%20Russian%20troops%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20April%207%2C%202024%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Schwan%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20have%20been%20strong%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nato.int%2Fcps%2Fen%2Fnatohq%2Ftopics_37750.htm%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemonstrations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20from%20NATO%20allies%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20these%20guarantees%20carry%20little%20weight%20without%20the%20promise%20of%20full%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20NATO%20membership%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20security%20guarantees%20for%20Ukraine%20are%20blatant%20lies%2C%26quot%3B%20Canadian%20analyst%20Michael%20MacKay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmhmck%2Fstatus%2F1798381690366333386%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BKeeping%20Ukraine%20out%20of%20NATO%20serves%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Russian%20terrorist%20state%20only.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELitra%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BUkraine%20relied%20on%20a%20similar%20'guarantee'%20without%20legal%20mechanisms%20under%20the%20Budapest%20Memorandum%2C%26quot%3B%20Litra%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftreaties.un.org%2FPages%2FshowDetails.aspx%3Fobjid%3D0800000280401fbb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%201994%20security%20assurances%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20Ukraine%20was%20required%20to%20hand%20over%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20in%20exchange%20for%20protection%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20Russia.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20Memorandum%20did%20nothing%20to%20prevent%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ukraine%20and%20some%20NATO%20members%20see%20these%20agreements%20as%20%26quot%3Binstruments%20to%20prepare%20Ukraine%20for%20NATO%20membership%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Litra%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20overall%20feeling%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Germany%20is%20that%20Ukraine's%20accession%20to%20NATO%20would%20be%20an%20escalation%20for%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Meister%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20alternative%20to%20NATO%20integration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20guara