ng%20to%20leave%20their%20countries.%20In%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Gaza%2C%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20always%20do%20what%20they%20need%20to%20do%20to%20protect%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wish%20there%20were%20more%20resources.%20Instead%20of%20just%20having%20background%20checks%20for%20prospective%20%26quot%3Bbuyers%26quot%3B%20or%20husbands%2C%20maybe%20access%20to%20international%20lawyers%20would%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20resources%20because%20when%20you%20come%20here%20as%20a%20foreigner%20and%20don't%20know%20the%20language%2C%20you're%20so%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20so%20detached%20from%20our%20culture%20and%20our%20family.%20The%20guy%20controls%20everything%20we%20do%2C%20including%20when%20we%20talk%20to%20our%20families%20and%20our%20friends.%20The%20community%20aspect%20is%20so%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverybody%20I%20talk%20to%20who%20grew%20up%20under%20similar%20circumstances%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20mental%20health%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObsessive-compulsive%20disorder%20(OCD)%20often%20stems%20from%20post-traumatic%20stress%20disorder%20(PTSD).%20I%20have%20severe%20OCD%2C%20including%20really%20bad%20looping%20thoughts.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20I%20know%20who%20shared%20similar%20upbringings%20also%20have%20OCD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cd787e0-f685-4ec7-a1fa-382a327a46a5%5C%22%3ESeeking%20help%20and%20moving%20forward%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20therapy%20for%20seven%20years%20now.%20I've%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-emdr%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEMDR%2520stands%2520for%2520Eye%2520Movement%2CInsider%2520and%2520start%2520reading%2520now.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEMDR%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20type%20of%20therapy%20where%20your%20eyes%20follow%20a%20light%20bar%20as%20you%20process%20your%20most%20traumatic%20memories.%20It's%20like%20exposure%20therapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20helps%20you%20become%20desensitized%20to%20your%20memories.%20So%2C%20I%20can%20talk%20about%20my%20turbulent%20upbringing%20without%20being%20triggered%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20healthy%20relationship%2C%20TikTok%2C%20writing%20my%20memoir%2C%20EMDR%2C%20and%20therapy%20have%20helped%20me%20be%20introspective%20and%20not%20live%20the%20same%20crazy%20life%20as%20my%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22tiktok%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20cite%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sincerelysuvorova%2Fvideo%2F7285807485309652270%5C%22%20data-video-id%3D%5C%227285807485309652270%5C%22%20data-embed-from%3D%5C%22oembed%5C%22%3E%20%3Csection%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sincerelysuvorova%3Frefer%3Dembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%40sincerelysuvorova%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%40sincerelysuvorova%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fmusic%2Foriginal-sound-7285807551210408750%3Frefer%3Dembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%99%AC%20original%20sound%20-%20katya%20suvorova%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%99%AC%20original%20sound%20-%20katya%20suvorova%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fsection%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20mom%20so%20much.%20And%20I%20recognize%20everything%20that%20she's%20done%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20left%20home%20when%20I%20was%2018%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20could%20never%20go%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20a%20boring%20life%20in%20Seattle%20now%2C%20and%20I%20haven't%20talked%20to%20my%20mom%20in%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20brave%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways.%20When%20I%20broke%20up%20with%20her%2C%20I%20think%20she%20was%20a%20little%20bit%20proud%20of%20me%20because%20she%20knew%20she%20was%20messed